OL,6,F"The panel considered Mr. Pitchfork to
OL,7,Fonly have limited internal controls
OL,8,Fand poor insight into his risky
OL,9,Fthinking and behaviour. It noted a new
OL,10,Fpreviously unidentified risk had been
OL,11,Fobserved in relation to his custodial
OL,12,Fbehaviour and that this was yet to be
OL,13,Fproperly explored or addressed.
OL,15,F"The panel considered that any further
OL,16,Foffence focused work would need to be
OL,17,Fcompleted in a closed prison. It did
OL,18,Fnot believe that Mr. Pitchfork had
OL,19,Fmade sufficient progress in addressing
OL,20,Fand reducing risk to a level that
OL,21,Fwould be
